edu.iastate.ansci.flip

Class Animal

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.iastate.ansci.flip.Animal
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>

    public class Animal
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>, java.io.Serializable
    The simulations analogue of a real-world animal.

    This is the object that is used for breeding using the information about its GenomeInfo and PseudoGenomeInfo that is established prior to creation.

    See Also:

        public Animal(Population pop,
              Breed breed,
              int birthCycle)
        Creates a founder using the allele frequencies from the given Breed. Its age is set according to the GenomeInfo#founderAgeDistribution. Either sex is equally likely.
        Parameters:
        breed - the desired breed for this founder

      • Animal

        public Animal(Population pop,
              Breed breed,
              double sexRatio,
              int birthCycle,
              boolean popSetup,
              boolean popSetupEmpty)
        Creates a founder using the allele frequencies from the given Breed. Its age is set according to the GenomeInfo#founderAgeDistribution. The sex is set via the provided female/male ratio.
        Parameters:
        breed - the desired breed for this founder
        sexRatio - the desired female/male ratio

      • Animal

        public Animal(Population pop,
              Animal clone,
              Animal surrogate)
        Creates a "copy" of an animal. The copy has the same genetic information, but may differ in environment leading to potential different performance values.
        Parameters:
        clone - the animal to copy
        surrogate - the animal that provides the maternal environment pre- and post-birth

      • Animal

        public Animal(Population pop,
              Animal sire,
              Animal dam,
              double sexRatio,
              int birthCycle)
        Creates an animal through "natural" mating or AI (no distinction is made at this level. Sire is the heterogametic parent, and dam is the homogametic parent. The sex is determined by the provided female/male sex ratio.
        Parameters:
        sire - the heterogametic parent
        dam - the homogametic parent
        sexRatio - the desired female/male ratio

      • Animal

        public Animal(Population pop,
              Animal sire,
              Animal dam,
              Animal surrogate,
              double sexRatio)
        Creates an animal through embryo transfer or similar process wherein the genetic mother is not the birth mother. This is distinct from cloning in that there are 2 genetic parents not just 1.
        Parameters:
        sire - the heterogametic parent
        dam - the homogametic parent
        surrogate - the animal providing the maternal environment before and after birth
        sexRatio - the desired female/male ratio

      • addOffspring

        public void addOffspring(Animal animal)
        Adds an offspring to this animal. The animal's idNum is placed in a "litter" vector which is then placed in the offspring map keyed by the current cycle.
        No checking is done to ensure that this animal is indeed one of the offspring's parents.
        Parameters:
        animal - the new offspring

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(java.lang.Object o)
        Useful for sorting animals. Each animal is compared via its idNum
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>
        Parameters:
        o - the animal to compare with
        Returns:
        an integer:

        >0 if comparison animal is "older" than this animal
        <0 if comparison animal is "younger" than this animal
        ==0 only if the two animals refer to the same individual

      • determineCurrentPhenotypes

        public boolean determineCurrentPhenotypes()
        Calculates, via determinePhenotype(edu.iastate.ansci.flip.PhenotypeInfo), the phenotypic values of this animal for the current cycle of pop. Also calculates the phenotypic values for previous cycles if necessary (only necessary in founders with nonzero ages). Ensures that animal is alive for the current cycle before calculating values, as dead animals should not have performance values. Moves dead animals to #nullHerd if they died more than 1 cycle ago
